Describe a short journey you often make that you really do not like
- where you go
- when you go there
- why you go there
- explain why you do not like the trip

I’d like to talk about a short journey that I have to make almost every day, which is my commute back home from work. I currently live in Ho Chi Minh City, specifically in Gò Vấp District, while my office is located in District 10, so it’s quite a distance.

I usually finish work at around 5 PM, which unfortunately coincides with the evening rush hour. Under normal conditions, the journey should take about 30 minutes, but during peak hours, it can easily stretch to over an hour.

The main reason I dislike this trip is the severe traffic congestion. As you may know, Ho Chi Minh City is notorious for its crowded streets, especially during rush hour. On top of that, the weather is often extremely hot, which makes the whole experience even more exhausting. Since I tend to sweat quite easily, I often arrive home feeling completely drained.

What frustrates me the most is the amount of time wasted just sitting in traffic. Instead of being productive or relaxing after a long day at work, I’m stuck on the road, breathing in polluted air from vehicle exhaust. This not only affects my mood but could also have long-term effects on my health.

Overall, although it’s a relatively short journey in terms of distance, it feels much longer and more stressful than it should be. I really hope that in the future, there will be better solutions to improve traffic conditions in the city.
